\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {9}{\ignorespaces Power-law fit of \ensuremath  {\mathrm  {CoV}}{} vs.\ \ensuremath  {\mathrm  {VR}}{} for the two campaigns. The \(30^\circ \) slope is steeper than the \(90^\circ \) slope, so each unit of \(\ensuremath  {\mathrm  {VR}}\) buys more mixing on the tilted geometry. The dashed green line marks the industrial \(\ensuremath  {\mathrm  {CoV}}\le 0.05\) acceptance threshold.}}{25}{figure.caption.26}\protected@file@percent }
